bottle-brand
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a substance, usually made up of tar and pitch used to brand sheep, the mark made on a sheep, and the activity involved in dispensing the brand.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: also bottle brand
